reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Decent shelf but painful assembly…
reviews.reviewText: The shelf is decent for the price and doesn’t look bad. You get a lot of shelf space and storage. My main gripes was assembly was painful. Some of the stickers fell off which made trying to find the right pieces to put together took longer than it should’ve. Then came to the realization you are given no extra screws or pins. Other furnitures and shelves I’ve order on Amazon seemed to give extra screws just in case. Not these folks. The quality of the wood (if can call it wood) was okay. A little wrapped but you get what you pay for. Would I purchase from these guys or this brand again? Hard no, even if this was half the price of what I’m looking for.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute little cabinet!
reviews.reviewText: Got this to hide all of our internet equipment and all the cables and cords. It does just that! Love it. Living room is less cluttered now. Not super sturdy but you shouldn’t be putting anything heavy in it/on it anyways.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Looks nice but not sturdy at all
reviews.reviewText: We put it together and its very wobbly even though we tightened it all the way. We tried taking the scres out and redoing it but it was the same result. It works for our mudroom where it doesnt need to be great but its really not worth the money overall. Not sure if it was just a bad set though because I have had other furniture from this company that is super sturdy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I had in mind for my kitchen
reviews.reviewText: I don't have much storage space in my kitchen and even less counter space so I've been looking for a hutch or buffet to handle things that end up on the table. This looked really good online and I thought if I had to, I could afford two cabinets. This was easy to assemble even without instructions and I didn't have any extra screws leftover. This cabinet fit perfectly in my kitchen and all the cookies, chips and bagels fit inside with room to spare.
